This monochromatic green button-down shirt is the first item in our Mes Chamoru Koleksion, which celebrates the timeless values and traditions of our ancestors. It features a modern, geometric interpretation of the “guihan dikiki” (small fish), intricately woven from coconut leaves, and honors the art of weaving, known as Lina’la’ Chamoru, which has been passed down through generations, connecting the past with the present.

  • Material: 100% Polyester
  • Sizes: S - 5XL

column3:
“Woven Together, rooted in culture” — diversity is our strength. 

This tee’s neutral color makes the deep green design stand out, representing the traditional leaves used for weaving on the islands. Guam and Hawaii, known as melting pots of the Pacific, are built on a rich history of cultural diversity, symbolized by the woven latte stone basket and surrounding details. Both islands honor their origins while recognizing that everything, from the food to the very people themselves, results from blending Asian and Islander customs and bloodlines across the Pacific.
column7: Adult, Cultural, Guam, latte, latte stone, T-Shirt, weaving

column3:
“From the islands, with Pride” — a tribute to the Pacific

The deep blue color honors the deep trenches and changing tides of the ocean that encompasses all of Micronesia, Polynesia, Melanesia, and Asia. While the galaide symbolizes the unity that connects all who call the Pacific home.
